model_explanation: the prosodic focus in S1 is on "APPLES," meaning that Sue didn’t get anything other than apples. S2 says Sue didn’t get bananas, which is consistent with this, since it confirms that Sue did not receive anything else besides apples.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ELLEN." This means Sam only gave oranges to Ellen and nobody else. S2 says Sam didn’t give Tom oranges, which is a separate fact about who else did or did not receive oranges. S2 doesn’t follow directly from S1; it’s independent information.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "TOM." This means that no one except Tom received apples. S2 confirms that Mary didn’t get apples, which is entailed by S1.
